PEC Award 2016\b0\f1\fs24\par
\lang1033\b\f0\fs22 The PEC Award 2016 goes to the Foundation for Freedom in Russia \lang4108\b0\f1\fs24\par
\lang1033\b\f0\fs22\par
\b0 Geneva, June 6 (PEC) \endash  The PEC Award 2016 is dedicated to the situation of freedom of expression in Russia. The PEC Award committee for the defense of journalists handed the award on Monday to \b Zhanna Nemtsova\b0  the eldest daughter of \b Boris Nemtsov,\b0  a Russian opposition leader killed on 27 February 2015 at the Kremlin Walls. The award was designated to the Foundation that she created last year.  \lang4108\f1\fs24\par
\lang1033\f0\fs22\par
\b Zhanna Nemtsova\b0 , a journalist specialised in economic affairs, was forced to leave Russia in May 2015 and went to Germany where she works at Deutsche Welle. She runs her own show the "Nemtsova.Interview". In 2015 she created the Foundation Boris Nemtsov for freedom supporting those who fight for the democratic rights in Russia in memory of her father\rquote s political heritage. Prior to the death of her father, Zhanna Nemtsova worked for the Russian TV channel RBC. \lang4108\f1\fs24\par
\lang1033\f0\fs22\par
At the Award ceremony at the Swiss Press Club in Geneva, \b Zhanna Nemtsova\b0  said that \ldblquote all mass media in Russia are now controlled by the Vladimir Poutin regime. It is a dangerous trend which could lead to an information vacuum. I believe firmly in the freedom of information to guarantee the economic, social and political development of any country.\rdblquote   \lang4108\f1\fs24\par
\lang1033\f0\fs22\par
On behalf of the PEC Award Committee, \b PEC Secretary-General Blaise Lempen \b0 noted that the choice of the daughter of \b Boris Nemtsov\b0  for the PEC annual award was designated as a symbol.\lang4108\f1\fs24\par
\lang1033\f0\fs22\par
\ldblquote A symbol of the defense of freedom of the press against the abusive power of any regime that does not accept criticism. The development of the situation in Russia is worrying and calls for deploring several repressive measures against the media in the past months,\rdblquote  added \b Lempen.\b0  \lang4108\f1\fs24\par
\lang1033\f0\fs22\par
In addition, he said, Russia has a pivotal role at the international level, especially in the Ukraine and Syria conflicts. \lang4108\f1\fs24\par
\lang1033\f0\fs22\par
\ldblquote Which makes its role more important in preserving freedom of expression and that Moscow assumes its responsibility for the protection of media during conflicts,\rdblquote  noted \b Lempen. \lang4108\b0\f1\fs24\par
\lang1033\f0\fs22\par
The PEC defends all journalists regardless of their nationality or political affiliation. In 2014, Russian journalists were killed in Ukraine and the PEC condemned those attacks. \lang4108\f1\fs24\par
\lang1033\f0\fs22\par
\b During 2015, 135 journalists were killed in 33 countries. Since the beginning of this year from January to May 49 journalists were killed while on duty. \lang4108\b0\f1\fs24\par
\lang1033\b\f0\fs22\par
The PEC calls upon all governments that such crimes undergo quick independent and impartial investigations and that the perpetrators of those crimes are brought to justice.   \lang4108\b0\f1\fs24\par
\lang1033\b\f0\fs22\par
PEC President Hedayat Abdel Nabi \b0 noted this is a moment of remembrance for all the fallen journalists in the line of duty.\b  Abdel Nabi \b0 added it is an annual wake up call to work for legal binding rules to protect journalists in conflict zones and other dangerous situations.   \lang4108\f1\fs24\par
\lang1033\f0\fs22  \lang4108\f1\fs24\par
\lang1033\f0\fs22 The PEC award 2016 is sponsored by the City of Geneva\b .\b0  The Award goes every year to a public figure or organisation that works for the protection of journalists for the previous year.   \lang4108\f1\fs24\par
\lang1033\f0\fs22\par
In \b 2015\b0  the Award was designated to the situation in Ukraine and the efforts of Mrs. Dunja Mijatovic, representative of the freedom of the media at the Organisation of security and Cooperation (OSCE) in Europe and Mrs. Liudmyla Zlobina, Director of Kiev Information Center - Crimean Center for Investigative Reporting. \lang4108\f1\fs24\par
\lang1033\f0\fs22\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sl240\slmult1\lang4108 The Award was given in \b 2014\b0  to the Swiss Foundation Hirondelle for its role in Central African Republic; in \b 2013\b0  to Media Cartoonist from Honduras, Allan McDonald and Ileana Alamilla, Director of the Centre for Information on Guatemala (Cerigua), the Austrian and Swiss Ambassadors to the UN in Geneva; in \b 2012\b0  to the representative of the Syrian Democrats \cf1 Dr Tawfik Chamaa and in absentia the director of the Syrian Center for media and freedom of expression (SCM) Mazen Darwish; in \b 2011\b0  to the\b  \b0 President of the Tunisian syndicate of journalists Neji Bghouri, to Ahmed Abdelaziz, representing the bloggers of the revolution of Egypt and to Khaled Saleh, on behalf of the NGO Libyan Human Rights Solidarity (LHRS); in \b 2010 \b0 to the families of the 32 slain journalists in the 23 November 2009 Maguindanao massacre in the Philippines, and earmarked to the Center for Media Freedom and Responsibility (CMFR) fund; in \b 2009\b0  to the Palestinian Center for development and media freedom (MADA) and the first President of the Human Rights Council and Ambassador of Mexico to the UN in Geneva Luis Alfonso de Alba.\cf0\f1\fs24\par
